column5: Okay so here are my two Jack O Lanterns (pumpkins)  IMG_0219 by Joeyfishing, on Flickr   Here was the bounty  IMG_0221 by Joeyfishing, on Flickr   Here is the outfit I bought for the shell out  IMG_0235 by Joeyfishing, on Flickr
Obviously not done by me Sorry copy didn't work
Not mine, but my favorite @ this time of year.

I love Halloween, looks like you do to Joey.  Butt mucher's eyes are pretty wide here.    Crappy pic but I carved my pumpkin this afternoon.     Me and my good friend next door neighbor set up the front yard. We have eerie music blasting, flood lights shooting back to the sidewalk so people can't see what's back there.    Chiminea burning and drinks in the back.    With little kids we take off our masks and be nice, with older kids we are merciless, no speaking,  jumping out of bushes, grabbing ankles while hidden in a pile of leaves, throwing cherry bombs in the chiminea etc    Love it! Neighbor bonding, fun, and no rain.

In our old neighbourhood , trick or treating was for all ages.   Mountains of goodies for the kids, and jello shooters up and down the street for the adults.  Yes, we showed no mercy with the older kids.  Kids stopped coming to our door for a few years. Some vague rumour about an axe wielding psycho?????
